---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ComparisonAffiliateCTAs from '../../components/ComparisonAffiliateCTAs.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  title: 'Framer vs Webflow AI',
  description: 'Framer vs Webflow: Which design-focused AI website builder is better? Compare features, pricing, learning curve, and overall value for designers.',
  date: 'January 2025'
};

const tools = [
  {
    name: 'Framer',
    score: 8.8,
    ease: 8.0,
    design: 9.5,
    ai: 8.5,
    price: '$15-35/mo',
    strengths: ['Gorgeous templates', 'Code export', 'Fast performance', 'Modern AI', 'Easier learning'],
    weaknesses: ['Learning curve', 'No native e-commerce', 'Design skill helps', 'Younger platform']
  },
  {
    name: 'Webflow',
    score: 8.5,
    ease: 6.5,
    design: 9.0,
    ai: 7.5,
    price: '$23-59/mo',
    strengths: ['Complete control', 'Powerful CMS', 'Professional results', 'Code export', 'Established'],
    weaknesses: ['Steep learning', 'Can get expensive', 'Not for beginners', 'Longer setup time']
  }
];
---

<Layout title={`${comparisonData.title}: Which is Better?`} description={comparisonData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Framer or Webflow better for designers?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Framer is easier to learn with a gentler curve (8.0/10 vs 6.5/10). Webflow offers more control but requires significant time investment. For most designers, Framer delivers better results faster. Choose Webflow if you need complete control over every pixel. Choose Framer if you want beautiful results without spending months learning."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is more expensive, Framer or Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Framer is $15-35/month. Webflow is $23-59/month. Framer has better entry-level pricing. Both offer code export. Webflow gets expensive quickly as you need more features. For most users, Framer delivers better value - you get similar results for less money and less time investment."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can beginners use Framer or Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Neither is ideal for beginners. Framer is easier but still has a learning curve. Webflow is complex and not beginner-friendly. If you're a beginner without design skills, consider Squarespace, Wix, or Durable instead. Framer and Webflow are for people willing to invest time in learning design tools."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do Framer and Webflow support code export?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. Both Framer and Webflow allow code export. This is a major advantage over closed platforms. You can build your site, export clean React/HTML code, and host anywhere. This makes both platforms future-proof for growing businesses."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which has better AI features, Framer or Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Framer has more advanced AI features (8.5/10 vs 7.5/10). Framer's AI can generate entire site sections, suggest layouts, and create content variations. Webflow has basic AI features but focuses more on manual control. If AI-powered generation matters to you, Framer is the clear winner."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I sell products with Framer or Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow has native e-commerce features. Framer requires third-party integration (Shopify, Gumroad). If selling products is central to your business, Webflow has the advantage. For simple product pages, Framer with Gumroad works fine. For complex stores, Webflow or dedicated e-commerce platforms are better."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does it take to learn Framer vs Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Framer takes 1-2 weeks to become productive. Webflow takes 1-3 months for proficiency. The difference is significant. Framer's learning curve is gentler because it works like design tools you already know. Webflow requires understanding web development concepts like CSS box model, flexbox, and responsive design principles."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <!-- BRUTALIST HERO: DESIGN POWER VS CONTROL -->
    <section class="relative overflow-hidden mb-16">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-950 via-gray-950 to-zinc-950"></div>
      <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-20" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F43F5E 0px, #F43F5E 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>

      <div class="relative z-10">
        <p class="text-[#F43F5E] font-black text-sm md:text-base uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">Comparison</p>

        <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-white mb-8">
          <span class="block">Design Power</span>
          <span class="block text-[#F43F5E] mt-4">Or Control</span>
        </h1>

        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-300 max-w-2xl font-medium leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Two design-focused AI builders fighting for creative professionals.
          <span class="text-[#F43F5E] font-bold">One wins on speed, one on control.</span>
          Both export code.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm font-black text-white">
          <span class="bg-[#F43F5E] px-4 py-2 border-[2px] border-white">Framer: 8.8/10</span>
          <span class="bg-gray-700 px-4 py-2 border-[2px] border-white">Webflow: 8.5/10</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- QUICK ANSWER -->
    <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6 md:p-8 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Quick Answer</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">
            <span class="text-[#F43F5E]">Framer wins</span> for 80% of designers.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg">Better templates, faster learning curve, more modern AI. You get beautiful results in days instead of months.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
            <span class="text-gray-700">Webflow wins</span> for complex projects.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Powerful CMS, native e-commerce, complete control. But requires 3x the learning time.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[#F43F5E]/10 border-l-[4px] border-[#F43F5E] p-4 mt-6">
          <p class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">THE BRUTAL TRUTH:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">Unless you're building complex web applications or content-heavy sites, Webflow's power is overkill. Framer delivers 90% of the results with 30% of the effort. For designers who value their time, Framer is the clear winner.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- AT A GLANCE -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">At A Glance</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="border-[3px] border-[#F43F5E] bg-white p-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#F43F5E] uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Framer</p>
          <p class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">8.8<span class="text-xl text-gray-500">/10</span></p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>1-2 weeks</strong> to proficiency</li>
            <li><strong>9.5/10</strong> design quality</li>
            <li><strong>$15-35/mo</strong> - Better value</li>
            <li><strong>Modern AI</strong> features</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 bg-white p-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Webflow</p>
          <p class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">8.5<span class="text-xl text-gray-500">/10</span></p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>1-3 months</strong> to proficiency</li>
            <li><strong>9.0/10</strong> design quality</li>
            <li><strong>$23-59/mo</strong> - More expensive</li>
            <li><strong>Powerful CMS</strong> features</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SCORE BREAKDOWN -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">Score Breakdown</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {tools.map(tool => (
          <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-200 bg-white p-6">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">{tool.name}</h3>
            <div class="text-5xl font-black text-[#F43F5E] mb-6">{tool.score}<span class="text-2xl text-gray-500">/10</span></div>
            <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
              <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-gray-100 pb-2">
                <span class="font-medium">Ease of Use</span>
                <span class="font-black text-lg">{tool.ease}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between items-center border-b border-gray-100 pb-2">
                <span class="font-medium">Design Quality</span>
                <span class="font-black text-lg">{tool.design}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between items-center pt-2">
                <span class="font-medium">AI Features</span>
                <span class="font-black text-lg">{tool.ai}/10</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t-2 border-gray-900">
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Price</div>
              <div class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">{tool.price}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PROS AND CONS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">Pros & Cons</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="border-[3px] border-[#F43F5E] bg-white p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Framer</h3>
          <div class="mb-4">
            <p class="text-xs font-black text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Strengths</p>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
              {tools[0].strengths.map(s => <li class="flex items-start"><span class="text-green-600 mr-2">✓</span>{s}</li>)}
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-black text-red-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Weaknesses</p>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
              {tools[0].weaknesses.map(w => <li class="flex items-start"><span class="text-red-600 mr-2">✗</span>{w}</li>)}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 bg-white p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Webflow</h3>
          <div class="mb-4">
            <p class="text-xs font-black text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Strengths</p>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
              {tools[1].strengths.map(s => <li class="flex items-start"><span class="text-green-600 mr-2">✓</span>{s}</li>)}
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-black text-red-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Weaknesses</p>
            <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
              {tools[1].weaknesses.map(w => <li class="flex items-start"><span class="text-red-600 mr-2">✗</span>{w}</li>)}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FEATURE COMPARISON TABLE -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">Feature Comparison</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto border-[3px] border-gray-300">
        <table class="w-full">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900 text-white">
              <th class="px-4 py-4 text-left font-black text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">Feature</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-4 text-center font-black text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">Framer</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-4 text-center font-black text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">Webflow</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="px-4 py-4 font-medium text-sm">Learning Curve</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center bg-[#F43F5E]/10 font-black text-sm">Easier (8/10)</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center text-sm">Steep (6.5/10)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-4 py-4 font-medium text-sm">Design Quality</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center bg-[#F43F5E]/10 font-black text-sm">9.5/10</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center text-sm">9.0/10</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="px-4 py-4 font-medium text-sm">Template Quality</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center bg-[#F43F5E]/10 font-black text-sm">Modern, trendy</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center text-sm">Professional, flexible</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-4 py-4 font-medium text-sm">CMS Features</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center text-sm">Basic CMS</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center bg-[#F43F5E]/10 font-black text-sm">Powerful CMS</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="px-4 py-4 font-medium text-sm">AI Features</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center bg-[#F43F5E]/10 font-black text-sm">Advanced AI</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center text-sm">Basic AI</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-4 py-4 font-medium text-sm">Code Export</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center bg-[#F43F5E]/10 font-black text-sm">Clean code</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center bg-[#F43F5E]/10 font-black text-sm">Production-ready</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
              <td class="px-4 py-4 font-medium text-sm">E-commerce</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center text-sm">3rd party</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center bg-[#F43F5E]/10 font-black text-sm">Native</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-4 py-4 font-black text-sm">Starting Price</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center bg-[#F43F5E]/10 font-black text-sm">$15/mo</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-4 text-center text-sm">$23/mo</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- KEY DIFFERENCES -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">Key Differences</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-[3px] border-[#F43F5E] bg-white p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Learning Investment</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Framer takes 1-2 weeks to become productive. Webflow takes 1-3 months for proficiency. The difference is massive - Framer gets you to results 4-6x faster.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600"><strong>Winner:</strong> <span class="text-[#F43F5E] font-black">Framer</span> - by a huge margin</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-200 bg-white p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Design Approach</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Framer is template-first - start with gorgeous templates and customize. Webflow is canvas-first - build from scratch with complete freedom. Framer is faster, Webflow is more flexible.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600"><strong>Winner:</strong> <span class="text-[#F43F5E] font-black">Framer</span> for speed, <span class="font-black">Webflow</span> for flexibility</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-200 bg-white p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">CMS Power</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Webflow has one of the most powerful CMS systems in visual website building. Framer's CMS is basic and functional. For content-heavy sites, Webflow dominates.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600"><strong>Winner:</strong> <span class="font-black">Webflow</span> - by a significant margin</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-200 bg-white p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Pricing</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Framer is $15-35/month vs Webflow's $23-59/month. Both offer code export. Webflow gets expensive quickly as you add features. Framer delivers better value for most users.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600"><strong>Winner:</strong> <span class="text-[#F43F5E] font-black">Framer</span> - better entry pricing</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- MY EXPERIENCE: THE LEARNING CURVE REALITY -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="relative overflow-hidden border-[3px] border-[#F43F5E] bg-white p-6 md:p-8">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F43F5E 0px, #F43F5E 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>

        <div class="relative z-10">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#F43F5E] uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">My Experience</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6 leading-tight">
            8-Week Learning<br/>vs. 8-Day Launch
          </h2>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">Real testing, not theoretical comparison</p>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">THE BEFORE</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">A junior designer wanted to build their portfolio. Had some design skills in Figma but zero web development experience. Same portfolio content, tested both platforms to see which was worth the time investment.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#F43F5E] uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">THE FRAMER ROUTE</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Created account, watched a single 20-minute tutorial. Used AI to generate portfolio structure in 3 minutes. Spent 2 days customizing - gradient backgrounds, smooth hover animations, project showcase with lightbox. Added case studies with image galleries and smooth scroll animations. Published on day 3. Site loaded in 0.9 seconds. Got 4 client inquiries first month = $8,400 in new projects.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">THE WEBFLOW ROUTE</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Created account, immediately enrolled in University.Webflow.com course (2 hours of video). Day 2: Still learning basics - box model, flexbox, Webflow's visual CSS system. Day 5: Built first 3 sections but struggling with responsive breakpoints. Day 10: Finally finished portfolio. Design was more polished than Framer - custom micro-interactions, pixel-perfect responsive behavior. But took 10x longer to reach the same outcome.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-red-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">THE ROI REALITY</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Framer portfolio launched in 3 days, generated $8,400 month 1. Webflow portfolio took 10 days to launch - lost 7 days of client acquisition time. At $8,400/month potential, that's $1,960 in lost revenue from delayed launch alone. Plus 40+ hours of learning time that could have been billable.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- 90-DAY BREAKDOWN -->
            <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">The Time & Revenue Breakdown</p>
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div>
                  <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Framer (Fast Route)</p>
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
                    <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-200 pb-2">
                      <span>Time to launch</span>
                      <span class="font-black">3 days</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-200 pb-2">
                      <span>Learning investment</span>
                      <span class="font-black">20 min</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-200 pb-2">
                      <span>Month 1 revenue</span>
                      <span class="font-black">$8,400</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex justify-between pt-2 border-t-2 border-gray-900">
                      <span class="font-black">Time value gained</span>
                      <span class="font-black text-green-600">27 days</span>
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Webflow (Control Route)</p>
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
                    <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-200 pb-2">
                      <span>Time to launch</span>
                      <span class="font-black">10 days</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-200 pb-2">
                      <span>Learning investment</span>
                      <span class="font-black">10+ hours</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-200 pb-2">
                      <span>Potential revenue</span>
                      <span class="font-black text-red-600">$6,440</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex justify-between pt-2 border-t-2 border-gray-900">
                      <span class="font-black">Opportunity cost</span>
                      <span class="font-black text-red-600">-$1,960</span>
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="mt-6 pt-4 border-t-2 border-[#F43F5E]">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Result:</strong> Framer saved 27 days and generated $1,960 more revenue in month 1. <span class="font-black text-[#F43F5E]">Webflow only wins when complexity demands it.</span></p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gray-100 border-l-[4px] border-gray-500 p-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-bold text-gray-900">WHEN WEBFLOW IS WORTH IT</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">A design agency needed their own site: 60+ case study pages, client login area, blog with custom filtering, team member profiles with dynamic filtering. Webflow handled everything. Framer would have hit limitations - CMS too basic for 60+ pages, no native client login, would need third-party tools. For 10-15% of complex projects, Webflow is key. For 85% of design work, Framer wins.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-[#F43F5E]/10 border-l-[4px] border-[#F43F5E] p-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-bold text-gray-900">THE LESSON</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">I've used both for 3+ years. Framer is my default - I launch 80% of projects in days instead of weeks. I only touch Webflow when the project demands complexity that Framer can't handle: multi-page platforms, web applications, heavy CMS needs. The learning curve difference is real and expensive.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
    <div class="mb-12">
